title: The real reason Boeing’s new plane crashed twice
description: Two Boeing airplanes have fallen out of the air and crashed in the past six months. On the surface, this is a technical failure. But the real story is about a company's desire to beat their rival.

title: Nintendo Game Boy Pocket review
description: Classic Game Room reviews the NINTENDO GAME BOY POCKET. The Gameboy Pocket does more than just fit in your pocket, it plays Game Boy games! Produced by Nintendo several years after the original, groundbreaking Nintendo Game Boy, the Game Boy Pocket is smaller, lighter, uses two AAA batteries and has a larger, better screen. The unit's smaller size makes it more portable and comfortable to play games on and is regarded as one of the best Game Boy models by fans.

title: Why Plane Tires Don't Explode On Landing

title: The sonic boom problem - Katerina Kaouri
description:
Objects that fly faster than the speed of sound (like really fast planes) create a shock wave accompanied by a thunder-like noise: the sonic boom. These epic sounds can cause distress to people and animals and even damage nearby buildings. Katerina Kaouri details how scientists use math to predict sonic booms' paths in the atmosphere, where they will land, and how loud they will be.

Lesson by Katerina Kaouri, animation by Anton Bogaty.
